title: To Leto
lines: Dark-veiled Leto, revered goddess, mother of twins, great-souled daughter of Koios, queen to whom many pray, to your lot fell the birth pains for Zeus' fair children, you bore Phoibos and arrow-pouring Artemis, her on Ortygia, him on rocky Delos.
Hear, lady goddess, come with favor in your heart to bring a sweet end to this all-holy rite.
